---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '../../components/Breadcrumb.astro';
import Alert from '../../components/Alert.astro';
import Accordion from '../../components/Accordion.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="Troubleshooting: Legitimate Sites Being Blocked"
	description="Fix false positives where important websites are blocked incorrectly. Learn how to whitelist sites and adjust filter sensitivity."
>
	<Breadcrumb />

	<div class="guide-container">
		<header class="guide-header">
			<div class="difficulty-badge beginner">Beginner</div>
			<h1>Legitimate Sites Being Blocked</h1>
			<p class="subtitle">
				Important websites are being blocked incorrectly (false positives). Learn how to whitelist sites and adjust filtering.
			</p>
			<div class="meta">
				<span>‚è±Ô∏è Time Required: 5-15 minutes</span>
				<span>üîß Difficulty: Beginner</span>
			</div>
		</header>

		<Alert type="warning">
			<strong>Before Unblocking:</strong> Verify the site is actually legitimate. Malicious sites often use trustworthy-looking names.
			Check the URL carefully for misspellings.
		</Alert>

		<section class="guide-section">
			<h2>Common False Positives</h2>
			<p>These legitimate sites are frequently blocked by overly aggressive filtering:</p>

			<ul>
				<li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Medical information sites, pharmacy portals</li>
				<li><strong>Education:</strong> School websites, online learning platforms</li>
				<li><strong>Finance:</strong> Banks, investment platforms, cryptocurrency exchanges</li>
				<li><strong>Government:</strong> Tax portals, DMV, social services</li>
				<li><strong>Shopping:</strong> Clothing retailers (sometimes blocked due to model photos)</li>
				<li><strong>Cloud storage:</strong> Google Drive, Dropbox, OneDrive sharing links</li>
				<li><strong>Forums:</strong> Reddit, Quora, Stack Overflow (user-generated content)</li>
			</ul>

			<p>
				False positives occur because filtering uses category-based blocking. A site might be classified in a blocked category
				even if it has legitimate uses.
			</p>
		</section>

		<section class="guide-section">
			<h2>Solutions by Filtering Method</h2>

			<div class="step">
				<h3><span class="step-number">1</span> OpenDNS Filtering</h3>

				<h4>Option A: Whitelist Individual Sites</h4>
				<ol>
					<li>Log into your OpenDNS account at <strong>dashboard.opendns.com</strong></li>
					<li>Select your network configuration</li>
					<li>Navigate to <strong>Web Content Filtering</strong></li>
					<li>Scroll to bottom: <strong>"Manage Individual Domains"</strong></li>
					<li>Under <strong>"Always Allow"</strong>, add the domain</li>
					<li>Example: Add <code>reddit.com</code> if needed for schoolwork</li>
					<li>Click <strong>"Add Domain"</strong></li>
					<li>Wait 3-5 minutes for changes to propagate</li>
				</ol>

				<h4>Option B: Adjust Category Sensitivity</h4>
				<ol>
					<li>Dashboard ‚Üí <strong>Web Content Filtering</strong></li>
					<li>Review blocked categories</li>
					<li>Uncheck categories that are blocking too broadly</li>
					<li>Example: If educational sites are blocked, uncheck "Forums/Bulletin Boards"</li>
					<li>Save changes</li>
				</ol>

				<Alert type="info">
					<strong>Note:</strong> OpenDNS FamilyShield (free version) cannot be customized. Upgrade to OpenDNS Home
					(free with signup) for whitelist control.
				</Alert>
			</div>

			<div class="step">
				<h3><span class="step-number">2</span> CleanBrowsing Filtering</h3>

				<h4>Free Filters (No Customization):</h4>
				<p>CleanBrowsing's free filters cannot be customized. Options:</p>
				<ul>
					<li><strong>Switch filter levels:</strong> Use "Adult" filter instead of "Family" filter (less restrictive)</li>
					<li><strong>Upgrade to paid:</strong> $5/month for custom whitelists</li>
					<li><strong>Device-specific bypass:</strong> Change DNS on specific devices only</li>
				</ul>

				<h4>Paid Plan Whitelisting:</h4>
				<ol>
					<li>Log into CleanBrowsing dashboard</li>
					<li>Select your filter profile</li>
					<li>Navigate to <strong>"Allowed Domains"</strong></li>
					<li>Add domain to allow list</li>
					<li>Can use wildcards: <code>*.example.com</code> allows all subdomains</li>
					<li>Save and wait 2-3 minutes</li>
				</ol>
			</div>

			<div class="step">
				<h3><span class="step-number">3</span> Router Parental Controls</h3>

				<h4>Most Routers:</h4>
				<ol>
					<li>Log into router admin panel</li>
					<li>Navigate to <strong>Parental Controls</strong> or <strong>Security</strong></li>
					<li>Find <strong>"Allowed Sites"</strong>, <strong>"Whitelist"</strong>, or <strong>"Exceptions"</strong></li>
					<li>Add the domain</li>
					<li>Apply changes and reboot router if necessary</li>
				</ol>

				<h4>ASUS Routers:</h4>
				<ol>
					<li>AiProtection ‚Üí Parental Controls</li>
					<li>Select profile</li>
					<li>Content Filter ‚Üí <strong>"URL Filter Exception"</strong></li>
					<li>Add allowed domain</li>
				</ol>

				<h4>Netgear Routers:</h4>
				<ol>
					<li>Security ‚Üí Parental Controls</li>
					<li>Click managed device</li>
					<li><strong>"Always Allow"</strong> section</li>
					<li>Add website</li>
				</ol>

				<h4>TP-Link Routers:</h4>
				<ol>
					<li>HomeCare ‚Üí Parental Controls</li>
					<li>Select profile</li>
					<li>Insights ‚Üí <strong>"Whitelisted"</strong></li>
					<li>Add site</li>
				</ol>
			</div>

			<div class="step">
				<h3><span class="step-number">4</span> Software Filtering (Qustodio, Net Nanny, etc.)</h3>

				<h4>Qustodio:</h4>
				<ol>
					<li>Log into family portal at <strong>family.qustodio.com</strong></li>
					<li>Select child's profile</li>
					<li><strong>Rules</strong> ‚Üí <strong>Web Filtering</strong></li>
					<li>Scroll to <strong>"Exceptions"</strong></li>
					<li><strong>"Always allow these sites"</strong> ‚Üí Add domain</li>
					<li>Changes apply immediately</li>
				</ol>

				<h4>Net Nanny:</h4>
				<ol>
					<li>Log into online dashboard</li>
					<li>Select family member</li>
					<li><strong>Web Settings</strong> ‚Üí <strong>"Allow List"</strong></li>
					<li>Add website</li>
					<li>Can allow temporarily or permanently</li>
				</ol>

				<h4>Bark:</h4>
				<ol>
					<li>Bark app or dashboard</li>
					<li>Child's profile ‚Üí <strong>Screen Time</strong></li>
					<li><strong>Website Rules</strong> ‚Üí <strong>"Allowed Websites"</strong></li>
					<li>Add site</li>
				</ol>

				<h4>Circle:</h4>
				<ol>
					<li>Circle app</li>
					<li>Select profile</li>
					<li><strong>Filter Level</strong> ‚Üí <strong>"Custom"</strong></li>
					<li><strong>"Allowed Sites"</strong> ‚Üí Add domain</li>
				</ol>
			</div>

			<div class="step">
				<h3><span class="step-number">5</span> Device-Level Controls</h3>

				<h4>iOS Screen Time:</h4>
				<ol>
					<li>Settings ‚Üí Screen Time ‚Üí Select child/device</li>
					<li><strong>Content & Privacy Restrictions</strong> ‚Üí <strong>Content Restrictions</strong></li>
					<li><strong>Web Content</strong> ‚Üí <strong>"Allowed Websites Only"</strong> or <strong>"Limit Adult Websites"</strong></li>
					<li>Under <strong>"Always Allow"</strong> section, tap <strong>Add Website</strong></li>
					<li>Enter site name and URL</li>
					<li>Done</li>
				</ol>

				<h4>Android Family Link:</h4>
				<ol>
					<li>Family Link app on parent device</li>
					<li>Select child</li>
					<li><strong>Manage Settings</strong> ‚Üí <strong>Filters on Google Chrome</strong></li>
					<li><strong>Manage Sites</strong> ‚Üí <strong>Approved</strong></li>
					<li>Add website</li>
				</ol>

				<h4>Windows Family Safety:</h4>
				<ol>
					<li>Visit <strong>account.microsoft.com/family</strong></li>
					<li>Select family member</li>
					<li><strong>Content Restrictions</strong> ‚Üí <strong>Web Browsing</strong></li>
					<li>Under <strong>"Always allow these"</strong></li>
					<li>Add URL</li>
				</ol>

				<h4>macOS Screen Time:</h4>
				<ol>
					<li>System Settings ‚Üí Screen Time</li>
					<li>Select user</li>
					<li><strong>Content & Privacy</strong> ‚Üí <strong>Web Content</strong></li>
					<li><strong>Allowed Websites Only</strong> ‚Üí Add <strong>+</strong></li>
					<li>Enter site details</li>
				</ol>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="guide-section">
			<h2>Temporary Access Solutions</h2>
			<p>When permanent whitelisting isn't appropriate but temporary access is needed:</p>

			<div class="accordion-list">
				<Accordion title="Timed Whitelist (Preferred)">
					<p>Some systems support temporary exceptions:</p>
					<ul>
						<li><strong>Net Nanny:</strong> "Allow for 1 hour" button when site is blocked</li>
						<li><strong>Bark:</strong> Can approve individual site access requests</li>
						<li><strong>Qustodio:</strong> "Pause Protection" for 5-60 minutes</li>
					</ul>
					<p>After time expires, filtering automatically resumes.</p>
				</Accordion>

				<Accordion title="Supervised Browsing">
					<p>Unblock temporarily while supervising:</p>
					<ol>
						<li>Disable filtering temporarily</li>
						<li>Sit with child while they access needed content</li>
						<li>Re-enable filtering when done</li>
					</ol>
					<p>Appropriate for school projects requiring research on sensitive topics.</p>
				</Accordion>

				<Accordion title="Alternative Device">
					<p>Use an unfiltered device for specific tasks:</p>
					<ul>
						<li>Parent's phone or laptop (supervised)</li>
						<li>School chromebook (school's filtering only)</li>
						<li>Public library computer</li>
					</ul>
					<p>Maintains filtering on child's personal devices.</p>
				</Accordion>

				<Accordion title="Request System">
					<p>Teach kids to request access:</p>
					<ol>
						<li>Child encounters blocked site</li>
						<li>Takes screenshot or notes URL</li>
						<li>Asks parent to review</li>
						<li>Parent decides whether to whitelist</li>
					</ol>
					<p>Builds communication and trust while maintaining protection.</p>
				</Accordion>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="guide-section">
			<h2>Decision Framework: To Unblock or Not?</h2>

			<h3>‚úÖ Unblock If:</h3>
			<ul>
				<li>Required for school/work</li>
				<li>Clearly legitimate business/service</li>
				<li>False positive due to broad category blocking</li>
				<li>Age-appropriate content for your child</li>
				<li>Reputable source (government, major brand, educational institution)</li>
			</ul>

			<h3>‚ö†Ô∏è Proceed Cautiously If:</h3>
			<ul>
				<li>User-generated content site (can contain anything)</li>
				<li>Social media platform</li>
				<li>Anonymous forum or imageboard</li>
				<li>Dating or relationship advice site</li>
				<li>Site discussing mature topics (even educationally)</li>
			</ul>
			<p><em>Consider: Supervised access only, not permanent whitelist</em></p>

			<h3>‚ùå Don't Unblock If:</h3>
			<ul>
				<li>You're unsure what the site contains</li>
				<li>URL looks suspicious or misspelled</li>
				<li>Child can't articulate a legitimate reason</li>
				<li>Site bypasses or discusses bypassing filters</li>
				<li>Proxy site, VPN service, or "unblock" tool</li>
			</ul>
		</section>

		<section class="guide-section">
			<h2>Common Scenarios</h2>

			<Accordion title="Reddit blocked but needed for homework">
				<p><strong>Problem:</strong> Teacher assigned research on specific subreddit, but Reddit is blocked.</p>
				<p><strong>Solutions:</strong></p>
				<ol>
					<li><strong>Best:</strong> Supervised access on parent's device</li>
					<li><strong>Alternative:</strong> Whitelist specific subreddit only (if filtering supports subdomain/path filtering)</li>
					<li><strong>Option 3:</strong> Contact teacher about alternative assignment</li>
				</ol>
				<Alert type="warning">
					Don't whitelist all of Reddit - it contains unmoderated content. Specific subreddits only.
				</Alert>
			</Accordion>

			<Accordion title="Bank website blocked">
				<p><strong>Problem:</strong> Online banking site flagged as financial/commerce.</p>
				<p><strong>Solution:</strong> Always whitelist legitimate financial institutions:</p>
				<ol>
					<li>Verify URL is correct (beware of phishing)</li>
					<li>Add to permanent whitelist</li>
					<li>Add both www and non-www versions</li>
					<li>Consider whitelisting entire financial category if using DNS filtering</li>
				</ol>
			</Accordion>

			<Accordion title="Online shopping sites blocked">
				<p><strong>Problem:</strong> Clothing/shoe retailers blocked due to model photos.</p>
				<p><strong>Assessment needed:</strong></p>
				<ul>
					<li><strong>Major retailers (Target, Old Navy, etc.):</strong> Usually safe to whitelist</li>
					<li><strong>Fashion sites with revealing images:</strong> Supervise first</li>
					<li><strong>Victoria's Secret, lingerie sites:</strong> Age-dependent decision</li>
				</ul>
				<p>Consider: Is online shopping necessary, or can child shop in-store?</p>
			</Accordion>

			<Accordion title="Educational sites about health/anatomy">
				<p><strong>Problem:</strong> Age-appropriate health education sites blocked.</p>
				<p><strong>Legitimate sites to consider whitelisting:</strong></p>
				<ul>
					<li>KidsHealth.org</li>
					<li>TeensHealth.org</li>
					<li>Planned Parenthood educational resources (age-dependent)</li>
					<li>Mayo Clinic, WebMD</li>
					<li>Approved school health curriculum sites</li>
				</ul>
				<p>Better to provide accurate health information than force kids to unsafe sources.</p>
			</Accordion>

			<Accordion title="YouTube blocked but need specific educational video">
				<p><strong>Problem:</strong> YouTube entirely blocked, but teacher assigned a specific video.</p>
				<p><strong>Solutions:</strong></p>
				<ol>
					<li><strong>Best:</strong> Use YouTube Kids or Restricted Mode with supervised access</li>
					<li><strong>Alternative:</strong> Parent downloads video, watches together</li>
					<li><strong>Last resort:</strong> Temporarily disable filtering, watch video, re-enable</li>
				</ol>
				<p>See our <a href="/guides/youtube-filtering">YouTube filtering guide</a> for better long-term solutions.</p>
			</Accordion>
		</section>

		<section class="guide-section">
			<h2>Prevention Tips</h2>
			<ul class="checklist">
				<li>Pre-whitelist common legitimate sites before issues arise</li>
				<li>Create a family process for requesting site access</li>
				<li>Review block logs weekly to catch false positives early</li>
				<li>Document all whitelisted sites and reasons</li>
				<li>Use least restrictive filter level that still provides protection</li>
				<li>Consider age-appropriate filter adjustments as kids mature</li>
				<li>Teach kids to ask before trying to bypass filters</li>
			</ul>
		</section>

		<div class="related-guides">
			<h2>Related Guides</h2>
			<div class="related-grid">
				<a href="/troubleshooting/child-bypassed-filter" class="related-card">
					<h3>Child Bypassed Filter</h3>
					<p>What to do when filters are circumvented</p>
				</a>
				<a href="/guides/dns-filtering" class="related-card">
					<h3>DNS Filtering Setup</h3>
					<p>Configure filtering with appropriate sensitivity</p>
				</a>
				<a href="/faq" class="related-card">
					<h3>Frequently Asked Questions</h3>
					<p>More filtering questions answered</p>
				</a>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</Layout>

